benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid Request: Multiple scenarios validate successful retrieval with defaults and various valid filter combinations (TC01–TC10, TC22, TC23).
Empty Response: Covered for no data and filters excluding all data (TC11, TC29).
Query Parameters: Broad coverage of accountId, queueName, serviceName, date range, defaulted flags, and invalid inputs (TC02–TC10, TC13, TC14, TC24, TC25).
Content Type: Validated application/octet-stream for success (TC01).
Error Handling: 400 for invalid accountId and malformed date, 404 for account not found, 500/503/504 server-side errors (TC13, TC14, TC25, TC30, TC16, TC19).
Security/Hardening: Injection/XSS input handling and resilience (TC17, TC26).
Performance/Scalability: Large dataset handling and latency expectation (TC18).
Concurrency/Resilience: Concurrent requests and transient failure recovery (TC20, TC27).
Regression/Defaults: Flag defaults and prior bug regression for withHistory (TC01, TC21, TC22).
gaps: Pagination: No tests for paging behavior (e.g., limit/offset, next links) with large datasets.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No scenarios validating 429 or graceful degradation under bursts.
Caching Behavior: No checks for ETag/If-None-Match or Cache-Control headers on successful responses.
Authorization 403: No coverage for authenticated but unauthorized user/role (forbidden).
Parameter Validation - Booleans: No tests for invalid boolean values (e.g., withHistory=maybe) or case sensitivity.
Date Validation - Logical Range: No test for minDate > maxDate returning proper error.
Content Negotiation/Headers: Only TC01 asserts content type; other scenarios do not verify headers consistently (e.g., charset, content-disposition if applicable).
Response Schema for Errors: Although TC28 mentions JSON schema, there is no concrete validation of error payload structure across 4xx/5xx cases.
recommendations: Add pagination scenarios: large dataset with limit/offset, verify total/next/prev (if supported), and stable ordering.
Add rate-limiting tests: send burst of requests to validate 429 Too Many Requests and Retry-After header.
Add caching tests: verify ETag/Last-Modified and 304 responses with If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since; assert Cache-Control on success.
Add 403 authorization scenario: authenticated user lacking admin privileges receives 403.
Add invalid boolean tests: withHistory=foo, withNotifications=1, case variation (True/TRUE) and ensure 400 or normalization per spec.
Add date logic test: minDate later than maxDate returns 400 with clear error message.
Strengthen header checks: assert application/octet-stream consistently, and any required headers (Content-Length, Content-Disposition) for binary payloads.
Standardize error schema validation: assert error JSON structure (code, message, details, requestId) for 400/401/403/404/429/500/503/504 across tests.
